HEADWORD: speakeasy
<hw>speak"eas`y</hw>, <pr>(sp⟦emac⟧k"⟦emac⟧`z⟦esl⟧)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>An establishment where alcoholic beverages were sold and drunk
illegally, especially one operating during the prohibition era in the
U.S. (1920-1932); a tavern or nightclub illegally selling alcoholic
beverages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

